                                If you simply pay your ticket without fighting in court, it means that you are admitting guilt and it will be counted as a conviction on your record, which can become the cause of many problems. If you have many points on your driving record, you have to pay Surcharges to the NJMVC. Surcharges are additional fines charged by NJMVC to the drivers who do not have a clean driving record. 
       
